Rating: 2
I agree that adding anchovies and capers would be a nice, traditional touch for another night, although this was simple and delicious as is. You may also wish to consider using Pecorino-Romano cheese rather than Parmesan - Pecorino is stronger, more pungent, and better able to stand up to big flavors like those found in this dish. The only change I made otherwise was using whole no-salt-added tomatoes packed in juice (crushed before adding to the pan and maybe compensating with more spices/minced garlic/salt) instead of stewed tomatoes: this way, you can control the saltiness, spicing and texture of the sauce, and have the satisfaction of knowing exactly what went into your dinner.

