Rating: 4
Made this for the first time tonight. Instead of any anchovies, I first fried 1/2 pound of Jimmy Dean's pork sausage in a non-stick skillet, and broke it up as it cooked; then added water to the broken up cooked sausage, and fried this mixture again. Drained it very well to get rid of excess fat. Then added the garlic, red pepper, olives to the skillet,and fried this mixture until the garlic was golden brown. Never needed to use any oil, or any added salt. Used 1 can regular diced tomatoes and 1 can of no-salt added tomatoes (which I had to chop). I feel that this version of the original recipe is a bit lower in sodium and fat than the original recipe, and it was WONDERFUL!!! Yum, Yum

