Rating: 3
I agree with those who suggested turning this into a puttanesca sauce with the addition of anchovies and capers. I made a further addition: a good teaspoon of whole green peppercorns, the kind that come packed in vinegar. With the anchovies, you'll want to omit the salt (at least till you taste it), and maybe the cheese, too. Don't skimp on the olives, in quality or quantity! Of course, this is no dish for a subtle wine. Maybe a slightly-too-young Chianti Classico, still a bit on the harsh side, or a young Barbera. A green salad before, and something rich and chocolate for dessert (since the meal is otherwise reasonably low in fat, especially of the saturated variety), and everyone should be happy.

